tip.text: I like how well they served family with a little kid. The interior design looked a bit much but it was cozy enough to enjoy our authentic German meals. I had Saurländer Zander and it was nice!
A nice bookstore in Horsens, Denmark. I went there to get the children book written by my friend and they have really helpful staff. Check the events they have for more literary feasts in Denmark.
A nice place to give and / or buy good quality second hand stuff where the profit goes to charity. There are others in Stockholm and this one in Spånga opens on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday.
A splendid experience to enjoy the view of Dubai from above. The observation deck is on the 124th floor (not on top) with a free wifi (ATT). Loved the cafe on the ground floor and the helpful staff!
Fancy mall! Loved the shops and Feast Village! If you stay at JW Marriott upstairs and forget some stuff, you won't find any convenience store or supermarket here. Go across to Pavilion Mall instead.
Don't get put off by the dodgy alley, narrow stairs and cramped office! They do nice and quick service! Ask for the recycle program. The options can be cheaper than fixing your point & shoot camera.

location.address: Ruko Dharmawangsa Sqr. Jl.Dharmawangsa VI No.35 lt
formattedAddress: Ruko Dharmawangsa Sqr. Jl.Dharmawangsa VI No.35 lt

tip.text: They performed 'Panta Rhei II' at Erasmus Huis Jakarta. Recommended one! Beautifully done by friendly performers. Tips for the show: Take photos before & /or after the performance. Avoid corner seats!
Among a handful of restaurants with a view overlooking the famous volcano & lake in Kintamani, this is one of the few that is 'halal' a.k.a. no pork. Buffet with a better service than the rest, IMHO.

Enjoyed the Insignia wine launch here! The service was quite impressive too! I found a piece of plastic inside my fish & they replaced it with a new one. I wish they had a non-smoking section, though.

formattedAddress: Wisma Kodel, GF (Jl. HR Rasuna Said Kav. B-4)
location.crossStreet: Jl. HR Rasuna Said Kav. B-4

tip.text: Their hot chocolate is one of a kind & the Ensaymada is high on my list of soulful delicacies! The way we're asked to keep our notes on the tables made my visit to Manila even more memorable! I ♥ it!

formattedAddress: Ground Flr, Greenbelt 2 (btwn Paseo de Roxas & Greenbelt Dr.)
location.crossStreet: btwn Paseo de Roxas & Greenbelt Dr.

tip.text: A beautiful uninhabited island near Manado (in North Minahasa region). It's nice for picnic or as a part of a diving track together with the big islands - Gangga, Bunaken, etc. Do bring enough water!
Excellent service! If the book you want is available at the other branch, they'll get it for you - free of charge! You can wait there or at Casa restaurant upstairs. Lovely membership programs too!
A médiathèque with helpful staff. Take your time checking the useful facilities to learn the language both actively (speaking - writing) & passively (reading - listening). On Monday, it opens at 2pm.

formattedAddress: Swiss-Belhotel Maleosan Manado (Jl. Jend. Sudirman Kav. 85-87)

tip.text: It was pretty impressive when the restaurant manager went around to offer service! I also appreciate the effort in combining Manadonese & Italian menus. It left a lot of rooms for improvement though.

formattedAddress: Kawasan Foodcity Mega Mas (Jl. Abdurachman Wahid)

tip.text: One of the reliable camera stores in Manado with a cheaper price than in the capital at times. Nice service from knowledgable staff. As always, call first to make sure they have the gear you want.

The books are okay and the service is nice. Food? Not so much! It's good for book club meetings where the members can also enjoy free wi-fi, snacks and musics. For a quiet place to read? Go elsewhere!

I agree that this restaurant's service could be better but then again, being extra patient when dining at a high demand restaurant might be worth it. Average food & beverage. The place is nice though.

location.address: Fairgrounds, Sudirman Central Business District Lot 14
formattedAddress: Fairgrounds, Sudirman Central Business District Lot 14 (Jl. Jenderal Sudirman Kav. 52-53)

tip.text: A group of baby sitters accompanying the families they work for having lunch & being treated as nice as others in this restaurant. I like that!! Food is nice. Marinated chicken is highly recommended!
A nice restaurant to hang out & enjoy meals in Batavia old square. The area can be a bit crowded at night so Sunday brunch is the best. Food & beverages are okay. NEVER underestimate their cocktails!

formattedAddress: Jalan Pintu Besar Utara No. 14 (Taman Fatahillah)

tip.text: Buffet has a nice spread. Loved the fresh honey! Friendly service as well. Unfortunately, there were so many flies outside so enjoying the table 'inside' the pool was a no go.

location.address: Holiday Inn Mai Khao Beach Phuket
formattedAddress: Holiday Inn Mai Khao Beach Phuket

tip.text: A nice hotel with a beautiful dock located on the mainland across Bunaken National Park. It's faster to get a boat from here to Bunaken as well as the nearby islands than from the city harbor.

This volcano is famous for the 3 coloured crater lakes on top of it. Amazing sunrise! Not hard to climb since one can take a car about halfway to the top. No clear direction signs though so ask first!
Caesar salad is one of my favorite appetizers and this place has the best one in my book so far. Excellent wine! Corn soup and salmon steak are good too! A bit expensive but absolutely worth it!

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, Level 4 #413 (Jl. Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: When it comes to Starbucks in Bangkok, this is my favorite! Friendliest staff ever! Cozy place too! The 'no camera' sign on the door is a bit confusing though. And if we can't use mobile here? Oh my!!

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

venue.name: Starbucks (สตาร์บัคส์)

tip.text: In my opinion, the old terminals have better executive lounges! This one is an eco friendly terminal? If so, it should've had a good air circulation system! Hot never goes well with delays & jet lags!
Only opens at weekends with an open air cinema every other week. It's got an array of delectable dishes & cocktails that come in a great service. Enjoying them under Jakarta's skyscrapers is a bliss!

formattedAddress: The Ritz-Carlton Pacific Place, 8th Floor (Jl. Jenderal Sudirman Kav. 52-53)

tip.text: In favor of the 'think global act local' spirit, when it comes to do-it-yourself coffee, this is my choice so far. Several branches in Jakarta with quite knowledgeable staff. Try the beans from Papua!
This island has a lot to offer. 200 characters are not enough to describe them. So find something that makes you happy and just do it! :-)

Founded by an expat that helps Jakarta's street people who collect used household containers. The stuff are bought, cleaned & used to make bag & accessories. I like that I can buy them to support too!

Among more than a dozen Indonesian airports I've been to, this is the smallest one. A nice start for a journey around Flores island. No taxi. Instead, some drivers will offer you a ride for a 'price'.

venue.name: Fransiskus Xaverius Seda Airport (MOF) (Bandar Udara Fransiskus Xaverius Seda)

tip.text: One of the places near Jakarta for a getaway with family & friends. Rooms & restaurant are OK. Nice service (a surprised birthday cake et al) + more facilities (golf, pool, bicycles, ping pong, etc).

Grateful for the helpful customer service! Otherwise, it'd be ironic to get around the city just fine yet get lost in its big mall. No lobby with many people sell stuff right outside the square? Ummm!

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

venue.name: CentralWorld (เซ็นทรัลเวิลด์)

tip.text: First they have THE tea. Second they have baked-to-perfection macaroons. Third they have lusty dishes. Enjoying all that in an elegance way of dining? All there's left to say is: Count me in!
A nice place to buy gadgets or have yours fixed. Cameras, computers, phones, you name it! I like that it's located in the business district yet not as crowded as the other IT centers in Jakarta.

Stayed here during a national blogging conference with participants from other countries in JAN 2011. It has a big conference room, attentive staff, nice room & restaurant. Bad signal coverage though.
I enjoyed the spicy spaghetti & lasagna in this cafe. Quite a nice list of beverages too! They somehow made up for the slow service. IMO, it is good enough for a relaxing afternoon in Bangkok.

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

tip.text: Nice meet-up place with a more reliable wi-fi. But if you want to hang out longer, better go up to the one in front of Kinokuniya bookstore since they have a better service than this one.

location.address: SOGO at Plaza Senayan, Ground Floor
formattedAddress: SOGO at Plaza Senayan, Ground Floor (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: Loved how I can see sunrise & sunset from this beach area in Penang! It's located adjacent to Teluk Bahang & Tanjung Bungah with hotels, restaurants, souvenir stores & fun activities for everybody.

I grew up with cendol (as we called it in Indonesia). Having the chendul here was a nice down-the-memory-lane experience! I prefer having it without red bean, just like the good old days! Pretty cool!
One of my favorites at The Shoppes. Reason being, that it's got nice menu for homesick remedies. Rijstafel, Belado, Sate Ayam, nom nom nom!!! Service is quite nice even when it's a bit crowded.

formattedAddress: #01-81 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands, (2 Bayfront Ave)
location.address: #01-81 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands,

tip.text: It's quite a good restaurant in Kuta. Food & beverages are OK. The Balinese chicken is spicy but nice. The tables by the front windows have a nice view of the pool with Kuta beach in the background.

The only SISTIC authorised agent in Jakarta (so far) to get your SISTIC tickets before flying to Singapore. There's extra charge so it's no use if you're buying in bulks. Friendly service nonetheless!

formattedAddress: Senayan City, Unit L-12C (Jl. Asia Afrika Lot 19)

tip.text: A nice legendary Chinese food restaurant in Manado. I mostly have it as takeaway instead of eating there. Butter chicken and Cap Cay are long time favorites! Their service is pretty fast too!
Nice theatre! I enjoyed the French Animation Film Festival in March 2012. There should've been a better coordination among the staff though. Different schedules depends on who answered your call!
Loved the weekly Italian movie here! Say you miss one, you can call the library to ask if the movie is still available. It's also one of the venues for the annual European movie festival in Jakarta.
Loved the chocolate pudding, oxtail soup and wi-fi connection!

formattedAddress: Kawasan Mega Mas (Jl. Laksda John Lie)

tip.text: Oh, for the love of lobsters and steaks!! They definitely do the name of the restaurant justice! The choices of music could be better though.
Nice and clean facilities with a matching service! Yes, it's worth it!

location.address: Holiday Inn Resort Mai Khao Beach Phuket
formattedAddress: Holiday Inn Resort Mai Khao Beach Phuket

tip.text: This place is why Hyatt Erawan is my favorite Hyatt in South East Asia. Unique venue for special event with complete facilities! Perfect for meeting & conference. Right next to a nice restaurant too!

formattedAddress: 494 Ratchadamri Rd. (at Grand Hyatt Erawan Bangkok)
กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

tip.text: My group went here to learn how to make ceramics in an open air studio with helpful English speaking guide and staff. The gallery and shop have beautiful collections. Nice open air restaurant as well!
A favorite for delicious local fried chicken in Manado. Unlike fast food chains that use 'ayam daging', this place use 'ayam kampung' - smaller but richer in taste. The avocado juice is yummy too!

location.address: Kompleks Wanea Plaza Blok J I-III
formattedAddress: Kompleks Wanea Plaza Blok J I-III (Jl. Sam Ratulangi)

tip.text: My favorite place to stay on Sentosa island. It has a library, a fusion of classic & modern designs, fantastic view from the pool, great restaurants & tranquil villas. Service is excellent as well!
It's not as big as other places but they have nice international performances and exhibitions every month. The sound system is okay. Friendly staff too! Get the monthly schedules at the front desk.

formattedAddress: Jl.HR Rasuna Said kav. S-3, Kuningan
location.address: Jl.HR Rasuna Said kav. S-3, Kuningan

tip.text: It has a lot of things to offer. I enjoyed the photography exhibition in March 2012, for instance! Great regular events with nice DJs too! A place to have fun no matter what time of the day it is. ;-)
A cozy corner to relax in between shopping at Plaza Senayan while enjoying a cup of cappuccino. For dining, I like their cream soup and tiramisu the most!
Loved their helpful service, bread, Tom Yum soup and wine - in that order! One of the best spots for people watching in Orchard? You can say that again!

formattedAddress: G/F Singapore Marriott Hotel, 320 Orchard Rd. (at Scotts Rd.)
location.address: G/F Singapore Marriott Hotel, 320 Orchard Rd.

tip.text: I wouldn't recommend the caesar salad - too much cheese so it's bitter! I love their tea & cocktail options though a bit similar to Union (same owner). Service? It's got its ups & downs.

formattedAddress: Oakwood Premier Cosmo (Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1)
location.crossStreet: Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1

tip.text: The place to go for both local & imported books in Jakarta. Good enough collection unless you are a student looking for more specific books. They've got several stores with monthly reward programs.

formattedAddress: Plaza Indonesia Extension, 5th Floor (Jl. Mohammad Husni Thamrin Kav. 28-30)

tip.text: One of the places to be 'lost in time' for bookworms and coffee lovers in Singapore! I love the coffee, lovely service, sofas, books and the cakes - in that order! Price is okay for a frequenter.
I like this Peter Saerang salon because they get things done faster than the other ones I've been to in Jakarta. Nice manicure & pedicure too! I don't smoke & so far, no smoking 'incident' for me.
The place to learn more about Batik in Jakarta. With a complete package, one can make Batik Tulis with a 'canting', learn Batik dance, Javanese culinary & 'Gamelan' music lessons. Quite professional!
The interior design makes the Balinese dining feel a bit more 'original'. The duck & chicken wings are nice. As a lover of spicy food, the meal is not complete without this set of 'sambal'.

formattedAddress: The Ubud Building (Jl. K.H. Agus Salim No. 132)

tip.text: Some wine they have here! Food and service are not bad either. The best part, in my honest opinion, is the live jazz on weekends. Very entertaining!

formattedAddress: Gandaria City, GF #M-G43 (Jl. Sultan Iskandar Muda)

tip.text: One of the oldest bakeries in Manado. 'Klappertaart' (coconut cake) is a regular favorite. For special occasions, try (as in order a day before) the more expensive 'Napolitein' (layered cake).

One of my favorite places to hang out in George Town. They have nice food and quite a good service. The one I love the most is, beyond doubt, the coffee. I always buy some boxes to bring home. Yummy!!

Instead of giving her phone #, a real lady makes the call AND it takes a real man to handle it! However, this & some small details of this restaurant, got me hooked. HARD! Food? OK. Live music? Nice!!

formattedAddress: The East, GF (Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Blok E3.2 No. 1)
location.crossStreet: Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Blok E3.2 No. 1

tip.text: Having xiao long bao in eight different colors & flavors is definitely a good reason to dine in this restaurant. All the noodles are yummy as well!

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, 5th Floor #CP 512-513 (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: As the most famous Manadonese food, 'Tinutuan' (vegetable porridge), can be found at small restaurants all over the city. This area is full of them where one can get Tinutuan way after breakfast hour!
When it comes to Union, I like it RED(dish). A glass of 'Life is good' smoothie or 'Cotton Candy' Cosmopolitan and some Red Velvet cake. Their Escargot is also worth the pennies. ;-)
It's on top of a hill so the sunset view overlooking a part of the city and seashore is nice! Food is good and not too spicy. Service is nice as well!
The food & beverages are standard. It is, however, a very nice place to enjoy sunset dinner by the beach in Jakarta. Reservation & a minimum order are a must if you want to sit at the 'front row'.

formattedAddress: Pantai Carnaval, Taman Impian Jaya Ancol (Jl. Lodan Timur No. 7)
location.address: Pantai Carnaval, Taman Impian Jaya Ancol

tip.text: It's got outdoor space right above a busy street with good buffet options. I'd go with a la carte. My set: Corn soup, Pasta, Creme brûlée and a glass of hot Cappuccino.

formattedAddress: Hotel Aryaduta Manado (Jl. Pierre Tendean Boulevard)

tip.text: The set menu came with free flow of iced tea with orange flavor which was nice enough. The roasted chicken was so so. I love the greek salad and chocolate mousse for dessert.

formattedAddress: Plaza Indonesia Extension, Level 1 Unit. E20-E21 (Jl. M. H. Thamrin Kav. 28-30)
location.address: Plaza Indonesia Extension, Level 1 Unit. E20-E21

tip.text: Lovely place to enjoy scrumptious meal with loved ones. No wine by glass option though. Try the Shrimp Fruit Salad, Thai Grilled Chicken Thigh & Klappertaart Sunda Kelapa for dessert.
The location is nice (on top of a hill near downtown). My favorites are Chicken Cordon Bleu for main course & Apple Pie with Vanilla ice cream for dessert. Stay away from the Tiramisu!!
One of the oldest supermarkets in Manado. So full of familiar people, one can expect a pat on the back while shopping. Not that complete. Service is nice, nonetheless.
Both the food and view are nice. Need I say more?
This Colonel's opens 24/7 with live music performance at weekend. There's also a delivery service. One of the options in Jakarta for after midnight food emergency? Could be!
Tapas at the waterfront is a bliss. The paella and mushroom are nice! I wouldn't recommend the sangria though. It tasted so weird, I regret I had it! Service is okay.
It opens around the clock. As the results, a lot of college students studying overnight! Be it a student or not, make sure you bring your chargers! Hopefully they'll have the weekly live jazz again.

formattedAddress: Menara Cakrawala, Ground Floor (Jalan Mohammad Husni Thamrin No. 9)

tip.text: Cozy place whether you need to get some things done online or just want to hang out. Sandwich is a bit too much. Coffee & hot chocolate are nice. Same goes with the service.
The sound of waves as the background 'music' mixed with the surrounding trees will make you feel at ease while enjoying your Japanese meal. Both the sushi and tempura sets are delicious!
The best thing about this restaurant is the sunset view! It's better to dine outside, of course. Furthermore, it has great food with a matching service! Fine dining at its best!
So far, this place has the best 'Stinco di agnello' (lamb steak) in my book! It is so tender, it melts the minute you bite it! Their 'Torta di carote' (carrot cake) is delicious too!
Reliable is how I describe the service provided by this store! Add that with a wide range of options they have no matter which 'religion' of camera you belong to? I keep coming back for more!
First of all, service is superb! As for the menu, their lamb is one of the best medium well steaks I've ever had. With a glass of Pinot Noir? Contentment!! I love their gelato too! Nom nom...
Coffee is okay. I can't say the same thing about the service though!
It has good options for Dutch dining in Jakarta with several branches around the city. The poffertjes taste good but the pancake is tasteless. Service is slow!
What I love the most is the interior design. Each room and its furniture bring back a lot of childhood memories! Food & service are nice. Favorites? Klappertaart & Poffertjes!
I'm a huge fan of the crepes in this restaurant! I simply can't get enough of them! My other recommendation would be their 'Grandpa Luigi' signature coffee. Lips smacking tasty!!

formattedAddress: Plaza Indonesia level 2 (Jl. M. H. Thamrin Kav. 28-30)

tip.text: A house turned into a restaurant and that's what so special about it: HOMEMADE Manadonese food! It's not as spicy as usual but the taste does the name justice. Thanks to my bestie who recommended it.
Joined a nice cooking class for expats in Mar 2011 before they officially started the program. Restaurant has nice menu & service. Loved the herbs in the shop too!

formattedAddress: Lone Crag Villa (595 Jln Tlk Bahang)

tip.text: It's one of my favorite places to unwind after a long day in Singapore. Beautiful view and nice drinks. Service is as great as the one in the restaurant underneath it!

location.address: 3 Fullerton Rd #04-01 The Waterboat House Rooftop
formattedAddress: 3 Fullerton Rd #04-01 The Waterboat House Rooftop

tip.text: Exquisite designs + delectable menu + excellent service (valet included) = time well spent! The Chef Menu with Duck Breast is a nice choice for dinner. Then go up for drinks at Prelude!
When it comes to buffet breakfast in Singapore, this is my favorite! Fresh food with a lot of options. I also appreciate the prompt & friendly service. I once had overcooked Nasi Lamak though.
Enjoying traditional food above the lake is a nice experience indeed! I love the brown rice! The crab and shrimp options are also delicious. Don't forget to book your table at weekends!

formattedAddress: Jl. Boulevard Bintaro Jaya, Blok B7/N1 (Taman Menteng - Kawasan Niaga Bintaro 7 Ciputat)
location.crossStreet: Taman Menteng - Kawasan Niaga Bintaro 7 Ciputat
location.address: Jl. Boulevard Bintaro Jaya, Blok B7/N1

tip.text: It's inside the parking lot of a mall but feels like eating right by a street! Loved the coffee! Food? Calamari & chicken wings! Service is a wee bit unpredictable = don't leave your patience at home.

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan CP 101B, Palm Gate Entrance (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)
location.address: Plaza Senayan CP 101B, Palm Gate Entrance

tip.text: The fish & chips was too big of a portion & the taste was so so. Coffee wasn't nice either. No problems with the service though. Good enough for killing time while waiting for your flight? Maybe not.

formattedAddress: Changi Airport Terminal 1 Viewing Mall, Level 3 (80 Airport Blvd)
location.address: Changi Airport Terminal 1 Viewing Mall, Level 3

tip.text: Food is average and service is full of 'incidents'. I do love their tiramisu cocktail - a very nice liquid dessert.

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, Palm Gate Entrance CP #101A (Jl. Asia Afrika No. 8)
location.address: Plaza Senayan, Palm Gate Entrance CP #101A

tip.text: One of my favorite dining experiences in Ubud. A long list of reasons: the rich in taste menu, rice fields background, beautiful gazebos, a lotus pond, live Balinese dance performance & nice service!

formattedAddress: Jalan Raya Goa Gajah (Banjar Teges Peliatan - Ubud)

tip.text: Also, it has a nice vintage design. Not to mention an inexpensive menu for a fine dining restaurant with a great location. Try 'Nasi Tus Tus' for main course & Cheese Pannekoek (pancake) for dessert.
One of the award winning restaurants in Lion city. It doesn't open for breakfast though. The pumpkin soup is absoYUMMYlutely!!

My favorite restaurant from Tugu Group! Each dining room gives you a different walking-down-the-memory-lane experience. Nice venue for a small party! I ♥ the 'Nasi Tjampoer' main course & Sla dessert.
At first visit, many people admitted this place gave them the creeps thanks to its mystical designs. It is a typical charm of restaurants from TUGU group! Try the Shrimp balls and Balinese Satay!
A nice arts center and a familiar place for meet-ups with friends for dining & a performance. I like the exhibitions & festivals as well! One horrible experience with a rude theatre usher though!
A nice restaurant to hang out & enjoy meals in Batavia old square. The area can be a bit crowded at night so Sunday brunch is the best. Food & beverages are okay. NEVER underestimate their cocktails!

formattedAddress: Jalan Pintu Besar Utara No. 14 (Taman Fatahillah)

tip.text: A nice place for meal & a 'view' if you sit on the top floor. Had my birthday lunch here & the food are nice; tacos, chicken wings & banana split for dessert. This chicken tandoori is too hard though.
The place to get Bentenan in Manado (traditional textile from North Sulawesi - Indonesia). They have complete collections including accessories made from the fabric. The service is friendly too!

Pretty well organized theatre even after the show is over. Like in other countries, seat shouldn't be a problem. Save $ on tickets? Invest in theatre binoculars! Front rows? Remember the 'spit range'!
One of the most favorite restaurants in Manado to buy 'Nasi Kuning' - traditional yellow rice. It's quite old but still going strong. Make sure they separate the chilly if you don't like spicy food!
My favorite is the salmon with mashed potato & butter creme that are simply perfect! They also have a pretty impressive service for a late supper.

location.address: Holiday Inn Resort Mai Khao Beach Phuket
formattedAddress: Holiday Inn Resort Mai Khao Beach Phuket

tip.text: One needs to climb down to get to the beach. Hotels & restaurants are on the cliff. Gorgeous view of sunset! One of the best places on Bali to celebrate a birthday in the 'nature'! ©Thesunsetgirl.com

formattedAddress: Jalan Labuan Sait, Pecatu Village (Jalan Padang-Padang)

tip.text: I led two tours for my expat friends here to learn more than just Batik. With proper arrangements, you'll get an English speaking guide, natural dye demonstration & traditional performance. Enjoyable!

formattedAddress: Jalan Aipda K.S Tubun No. 2 – 4 (Tanah Abang)

tip.text: Surely the place to unwind after playing all day at Kata beach! Loved the cocktails, beautiful crowds and of course, the sunset view!

venue.name: Re Ka Ta Beach Bar and Club

tip.text: The whole dining inside a chapel experience made this one of my favorite fine dining restaurants in Singapore. My set: Tuna Carpaccio, Salmon Roulade & Creme Brulee.
Old school but just like wine, the older the better! :-) My favorite is the crab cakes! Crunchy on the outside but tender on the inside. You can order half portion if it's too much!
Not only it has beautiful indoor and outdoor spaces, but it also has a long list of delicious Italian food to satisfy the taste buds. I love their pasta and bruschetta!

formattedAddress: Morrissey Hotel & Apartment (Jalan KH Wahid Hasyim No. 70)

tip.text: Love the dedicated buffet section for kids!! The sushi section is my favorite. Buffet comes with great options. Fresh juice is not a part of the beverages though.

formattedAddress: Shangri-La's Rasa Sentosa Resort (101 Siloso Rd.)

tip.text: Nice restaurant with a traditional touch. Loved the 'sate' and for beverages, I'd go with apple virgin mojito (soda). I wish it came in a bigger glass though.

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, 4th Floor #CP411 (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: I enjoy the 'view' at any restaurant in Oakwood more than the food & I can see on the tips here that I'm not the only one. But this place does have some delicious stuff to try. My fave? Mango chicken.

formattedAddress: Oakwood Premier Cozmo, Lt. 1 (Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1)
location.crossStreet: Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1

tip.text: Another Manadonese restaurant in J-town that is not too spicy. Needless to say, it's a favorite among my friends here. Loved the 'perkedel jagung' !!
One of the top 5 places for high tea in Singapore. There are several options. Try the English Rose Tea that comes with delicious cakes!
One of the best Manadonese restaurants in Jakarta. By that, I mean the spicy level is beyond belief! It feels like home indeed! Try ummm... everything?
It has several branches in Jakarta with delicious local food menu. The problem I have with this one? There were flies all over the place!! It made me lose both my appetite & willingness to come back!

formattedAddress: Jalan Tanah Abang II No. 76 (Cideng Timur)

tip.text: Unlike many restaurants inside the mall in Jakarta, this one doesn't serve breakfast. They open daily right before lunch time. Food is nice and service is exceptional.

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, 5th Floor (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: It used to be a nice hang out spot in the city thanks to its strategic location. The last time I went there (October 2011), I found a paper clip inside the ice cream on my pancake! Deteriorating? Yup!

formattedAddress: Djakarta Theater Building (Jl. M. H. Thamrin No. 9)

tip.text: A unique concept for dining, feels like hanging out with your friends inside your own apartment. The sofa next to the bed is my favorite spot. Try the lamb / salmon steak & mixed berries for dessert.

formattedAddress: Menara Gracia (Jalan H.R. Rasuna Said Kav. C-17)
location.crossStreet: Jalan H.R. Rasuna Said Kav. C-17

tip.text: I hadn't had so much fun seeing a concert in a long time! Moreover, everything was well organized, on schedule & no need to worry about safety no matter at what hour of the morning you're done!
